---
title: Tabs
---

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h1>Tabs</h1>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns"> 
    <h2>Box Tabs</h2>
    <p>Box tabs are used to display different content for an item. For example, on the Create Droplet screen, there are multiple tabs for different distribution types. Because we can not send the user to another page mid-creation, tabs are the perfect option.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns"> 
    <ul class="Tabs" role="tablist">
      <li role="presentation" class="is-active">
        <a href="#box1" aria-controls="box1" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Box #1</a>
      </li>
      <li role="presentation">
        <a href="#box2" aria-controls="box2" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Box #2</a>
      </li>
      <li role="presentation">
        <a href="#box3" aria-controls="box3" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Box #3</a>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="Tabs-content Tabs-content--box">
      <div role="tabpanel" class="Tabs-pane is-active" id="box1">
        Box #1
      </div>
      <div role="tabpanel" class="Tabs-pane" id="box2">
        Box #2
      </div>
      <div role="tabpanel" class="Tabs-pane" id="box3">
        Box #3
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

